
To build a new release, 4 steps are required. This will be enhanced in the future.

1. Update the version information.
Currently need to update multiple files.
1) The version in Makefile
2) Version in common/types.go
3) FireCampServerTaskdefinition Image in packaging/aws-cloudformation/firecamp-ecs.template
4) Update the cf-templates place to the release folder, CFS3KeyPrefix, in firecamp-master.template and firecamp-test.template

2. Docker Images
make docker to build the docker images for this release.

3. CloudFormation templates
1) Create the release "cf-templates" folder in the cloudstax S3 bucket.
2) Upload all template files in packaging/aws-cloudformation.

4. Packages
Update the rpm version in packaging/firecamp-dockervolume/rpm/firecamp-dockervolume.spec, and packaging/aws-cloudformation/firecamp-autoscalegroup.template.

make rpm to build the volume driver rpm.

1) Create the release "packages" folder in the cloudstax S3 bucket
2) Upload $GOPATH/bin/firecamp-service-cli.
3) Upload build/RPMS/x86_64/firecamp-dockervolume-*.x86_64.rpm.
4) If ECS agent is updated, please also upload it.
